



May it please Your Excellency
Chelsea [Mass.] Sept. 12th 1775 4 oClock P.M.



Enclosed are the Observations of yesterday & to day.1 I have observed that the Boat at Charlestown Ferry have passed more
[453]
frequently than usual last Night & this Morning Those from Boston to Charlestown being deeply Loaded with Soldiers & those the Contrary way with none. Nothing Remarkable Since my Last. I am Your Excellencys Most Obediant & Very Humb. Servnt

L. Baldwin Lieut. Coll

